    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>FOUR-DAY STRIKE PLANNED IN KOREA</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Samuel Len</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Len, Samuel</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>South Korea's Korean Confederation of Trade Unions calls for four-day strike this week to demand shorter workweeks and to protest possible takeover of ailing carmaker by a foreign company (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A South Korean labor group called for a four-day strike this week to demand shorter workweeks and to protest a possible takeover of an ailing carmaker by a foreign company. The Korean Confederation of Trade Unions, which claims a membership of 500,000, asked its members to walk off their jobs Wednesday through Saturday. If the government does not respond, the union said, it may prolong the strike.</p>
        <p>Samuel Len (NYT)</p>
      </block>
